article.headline: Catchings looks like star in making
article.linkText: Catchings scores 32 to lead Fever past Liberty
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Tamika Catchings decided the Indiana Fever
had lost enough.

	   Catchings had season highs with 32 points and 14 rebounds,
leading the Fever to a 71-62 victory over the New York Liberty on
Saturday night.

	   "Getting on the floor, going after loose balls, I'll do
whatever I can to help my team win,'' the WNBA rookie said.
"Whatever I can do, I will do.''

	   Catchings played the entire game, hitting 7-of-15 from the
field, including 4 of 7 3-pointers, and 14 of 16 free throws.

	   "It's just like that sometimes,'' Catchings said. "My
teammates just happened to get me the ball.''

	   Olympia Scott-Richardson added 12 points for the Fever (3-2).

	   Tamika Whitmore led New York (4-2) with 18 points. Vickie
Johnson added 13 and Tari Phillips 10.

	   "Tamika has a presence out on the court,'' Fever coach Nell
Fortner said. "I'm not sure if anybody can be ready for how Tamika
can play until they see her. The film doesn't do justice. You've
got to be out there and play against her to see for yourself.

	   "She just has a style about her that is very hard to stop.''

	   Fortner thought the game turned on one play with the Fever
leading 55-51 with just under four minutes to go.

	   Catchings chased a missed shot by one of her teammates out of
bounds, caught the ball in mid-air, then bounced it off Liberty
forward Sue Wicks. Scott-Richardson sank a layup on the continuing
possession, and the Fever completed a 16-6 run that pushed their
lead to 65-55 with 1:20 to play.

	   "I thought that was just a tremendous play, pretty much a
back-breaker,'' Fortner said.

	   Liberty coach Richie Adubato did not argue.

	   "We are seeing the makings of a superstar,'' he said of
Catchings, whose father is former NBA player Harvey Catchings.
"She has the total game, the total package.

	   "One very impressive thing tonight is her playing 40 minutes
tonight and 37 minutes last night. That's a lot of minutes. We had
no answer for her.''

	   New York went on a 13-2 run midway through the second half to
tie the score at 49-all, but Catchings scored eight points as the
Fever responded with the 16-6 run over the next five minutes.

	   New York took an 8-4 lead at the start, but Catchings scored the
next eight points as the Fever held the Liberty scoreless for more
than two minutes. Catchings scored 16 points in the first half as
the Fever took a 33-30 lead at the break.
